1
00:00:10,467 --> 00:00:12,300
<i> The explosion hit dad.</i>

2
00:00:12,433 --> 00:00:13,100
<i> What happened?</i>

3
00:00:13,233 --> 00:00:14,333
<i> Sorry, Boss.</i>

4
00:00:14,467 --> 00:00:15,467
<i>It seems the bomb that
was planted was too strong.</i>

5
00:00:15,600 --> 00:00:16,633
<i> Change of plans.</i>

6
00:00:16,767 --> 00:00:18,833
<i>It seems Vice Mayor Del Mundo
heard us talking.</i>

7
00:00:18,967 --> 00:00:20,800
<i> Order your men to dispose her.</i>

8
00:00:20,933 --> 00:00:21,867
<i> Housekeeping, Ma'am.</i>

9
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:23,367
<i>Can you just go back,
Mister, please?</i>

10
00:00:23,500 --> 00:00:25,067
<i>I need to.
I'm going to get scolded.</i>

11
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:26,933
<i>It'll probably only be a moment.</i>

12
00:00:27,067 --> 00:00:28,033
<i> Amo!</i>

13
00:00:28,167 --> 00:00:30,367
<i>Put that in your mouth!
Hurry up! Scratch Amo!</i>

14
00:00:34,133 --> 00:00:35,800
<i> You killed the Vice Mayor!</i>

15
00:00:35,933 --> 00:00:37,467
<i> No, I didn't do this!</i>

16
00:00:37,600 --> 00:00:38,733
<i>Sir, I'm going to call
the police!</i>

17
00:00:38,867 --> 00:00:41,067
<i>Miss, I'm a police officer.
I'm undercover.</i>

18
00:00:41,200 --> 00:00:43,933
<i>Tonyo, I accept if people
lose trust in me,</i>

19
00:00:44,067 --> 00:00:45,167
<i> but my own son...</i>

20
00:00:45,300 --> 00:00:47,600
<i>I also accept that there
are many murderers,</i>

21
00:00:47,733 --> 00:00:49,500
<i> but not my own father!</i>

22
00:00:49,633 --> 00:00:52,300
<i>Ma'am Enriquez, Lieutenant Conde
is here with Amo.</i>

23
00:00:52,433 --> 00:00:55,167
<i>Major, be careful
with your investigation.</i>

24
00:00:55,300 --> 00:00:57,333
<i> Make sure no one interferes.</i>

25
00:00:57,467 --> 00:00:59,433
<i>I believe that the truth
will come out.</i>

26
00:00:59,567 --> 00:01:00,967
<i> That's it, lock him up.</i>

27
00:01:01,100 --> 00:01:03,300
<i>Do you think, Sir, this is what
we've been waiting for?</i>

28
00:01:03,433 --> 00:01:04,800
<i> I don't know, Enriquez.</i>

29
00:01:09,033 --> 00:01:09,867
Are you okay?

30
00:01:11,867 --> 00:01:13,433
I'm okay, Sir.

31
00:01:13,567 --> 00:01:16,867
Maybe you need someone to talk
to or to drink with,

32
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:18,333
I'm right here.

33
00:01:23,133 --> 00:01:26,400
The person behind this
is already in jail.

34
00:01:26,533 --> 00:01:30,533
That's why I'm fine.

35
00:01:33,633 --> 00:01:38,067
But I won't refuse your offer
of one or two bottles, Sir,

36
00:01:38,200 --> 00:01:39,267
as long as it's your treat.

37
00:01:39,400 --> 00:01:40,700
Sure.

38
00:01:40,867 --> 00:01:42,933
Just one or two bottles only,
okay?

39
00:01:43,067 --> 00:01:44,967
We might finish a whole case.

40
00:01:49,933 --> 00:01:50,500
Sir.

41
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:56,333
Lieutenant Paloma,
what can Station 12 do for you?

42
00:01:56,467 --> 00:01:57,933
We need your help, Sir.

43
00:02:36,667 --> 00:02:40,033
This is the RGD Building under
the jurisdiction of Station 12.

44
00:02:41,067 --> 00:02:44,167
This is also the last known
location of the two women

45
00:02:44,300 --> 00:02:47,133
we suspect are victims
of human trafficking.

46
00:02:50,567 --> 00:02:53,100
I know that the building
is an office.

47
00:02:53,233 --> 00:02:54,733
Is that where they work?

48
00:02:54,867 --> 00:02:55,600
No.

49
00:02:58,300 --> 00:02:59,600
That's 6 Feet Under Bar.

50
00:03:00,567 --> 00:03:02,467
They've been operating in
the building for 3 months now.

51
00:03:02,600 --> 00:03:04,867
In the CCTV footage
we recovered,

52
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:07,700
the two victims were seen
entering the building,

53
00:03:07,833 --> 00:03:09,367
but they were not seen leaving.

54
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:15,567
What did the witnesses
who saw them at the bar say?

55
00:03:15,700 --> 00:03:17,433
That's our problem, Sir.

56
00:03:17,567 --> 00:03:21,033
There were no witnesses
who saw where they went.

57
00:03:21,200 --> 00:03:23,200
And there was no CCTV
in the basement parking lot.

58
00:03:24,267 --> 00:03:25,067
Conde...

59
00:03:26,267 --> 00:03:27,800
go with Lieutenant Paloma first.

60
00:03:28,833 --> 00:03:30,633
Check out the area.

61
00:03:30,767 --> 00:03:34,133
Then let's plan what we're going
to do.

62
00:03:35,333 --> 00:03:35,967
Yes, Sir.

63
00:03:42,700 --> 00:03:44,533
How about that?
Do you want that?

64
00:03:44,667 --> 00:03:47,333
- Yes, let's go with that.
- Okay.

65
00:03:47,467 --> 00:03:49,367
Village Chairman, we're next.

66
00:03:49,500 --> 00:03:50,867
I want fuchsia pink!

67
00:03:51,900 --> 00:03:53,667
I want purple.

68
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:54,967
I want that too!

69
00:03:55,133 --> 00:03:56,300
You're so envious!

70
00:03:56,433 --> 00:03:57,733
Ms. Britney!

71
00:03:58,600 --> 00:04:01,300
I knew it! I'll find you here!

72
00:04:01,433 --> 00:04:02,133
I'm here.

73
00:04:02,267 --> 00:04:03,333
You're shameless!

74
00:04:03,467 --> 00:04:05,567
You're a murderer!

75
00:04:05,700 --> 00:04:06,700
Who did you kill?

76
00:04:06,833 --> 00:04:07,833
I didn't kill anyone,
Village Chairman.

77
00:04:07,967 --> 00:04:10,467
What are you saying?
Look, you murdered my foot!

78
00:04:10,600 --> 00:04:13,567
- Yuck!
- Disgusting!

79
00:04:22,667 --> 00:04:25,467
Have you seen the CCTV
of the other establishment?

80
00:04:25,600 --> 00:04:28,067
Yes, still negative.

81
00:04:28,233 --> 00:04:30,500
But the bar, did you enter it?

82
00:04:30,633 --> 00:04:31,767
Just me.

83
00:04:31,900 --> 00:04:35,667
But that's the thing,
no one could ID the victims.

84
00:04:35,800 --> 00:04:38,467
Not even the bartender
or waiter, nothing.

85
00:04:38,600 --> 00:04:41,400
So the victim is probably
a first timer.

86
00:04:41,533 --> 00:04:43,067
Because if she's a regular,

87
00:04:43,200 --> 00:04:44,667
for sure someone will definitely
recognize her.

88
00:04:45,967 --> 00:04:48,167
That's probably the modus
operandi of criminals.

89
00:04:48,300 --> 00:04:52,300
Targeting newcomers
who have no companions.

90
00:04:52,433 --> 00:04:56,633
And they'll do it right when
it's time to take the victim.

91
00:04:58,100 --> 00:04:58,967
Above all...

92
00:05:01,033 --> 00:05:03,467
they only prey on women.

93
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:06,800
Let's go.

94
00:05:09,500 --> 00:05:11,400
So what happened to your foot?

95
00:05:11,533 --> 00:05:14,600
I just had an ingrown on my
toenail removed the other day.

96
00:05:14,733 --> 00:05:17,267
Then, that's what happened,
it's swollen!

97
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:18,500
Hey, you, Kendra,

98
00:05:18,633 --> 00:05:21,067
I had nothing to do with
that infection on your toe.

99
00:05:21,200 --> 00:05:22,500
The ingrown on your toenail
was so deep

100
00:05:22,633 --> 00:05:23,533
that's why you got injured.

101
00:05:23,667 --> 00:05:25,167
I don't care about
that infection.

102
00:05:25,300 --> 00:05:26,833
Maybe it's your fault
because you were careless,

103
00:05:26,967 --> 00:05:29,067
- that's why it got infected!
- What? It's my fault now?

104
00:05:29,200 --> 00:05:31,367
- You're really shameless!
- Wait a minute!

105
00:05:40,667 --> 00:05:42,467
There's so much clutter
on your desk.

106
00:05:43,533 --> 00:05:44,900
What's that? Unsolved cases?

107
00:05:46,467 --> 00:05:47,933
Don't you have anything to do?

108
00:05:49,567 --> 00:05:51,100
Yeah, just like you.

109
00:05:51,233 --> 00:05:53,600
There's still nothing you could
do about that bank robbery

110
00:05:53,733 --> 00:05:55,800
where your godmother died.

111
00:05:55,933 --> 00:05:57,233
Bobby, it's been months
already...

112
00:05:58,833 --> 00:06:01,600
or maybe the case that I brought
to you for help

113
00:06:01,733 --> 00:06:03,333
will be solved sooner
than the one you have.

114
00:06:04,500 --> 00:06:06,633
At least, us here
at Station 12...

115
00:06:07,833 --> 00:06:10,333
we don't need to ask for help
from other stations.

116
00:06:10,467 --> 00:06:12,567
We solve our own cases.

117
00:06:14,100 --> 00:06:15,067
Has it been solved already?

118
00:06:16,667 --> 00:06:18,867
Maybe you need help.

119
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:20,833
Just tell me, Bobby.

120
00:06:20,967 --> 00:06:22,400
Do you help? I'll help you.

121
00:06:23,567 --> 00:06:26,700
We don't need your help,
Lieutenant Samson.

122
00:06:26,833 --> 00:06:28,500
And how are you going to do that

123
00:06:28,633 --> 00:06:31,700
when you, yourself, are asking
for help from our station?

124
00:06:34,700 --> 00:06:37,400
Sir, we have a sting operation
in mind.

125
00:06:37,533 --> 00:06:39,700
Someone will pose
as a potential victim.

126
00:06:39,833 --> 00:06:43,367
The moment the criminal acts,
we will arrest them there.

127
00:06:45,033 --> 00:06:47,667
There is only one entrance and
exit to the basement parking.

128
00:06:47,800 --> 00:06:50,300
We can secure it so that no one
can escape.

129
00:06:51,333 --> 00:06:55,433
And one more thing, Sir,
they only prey on women.

130
00:06:55,567 --> 00:06:58,933
So what now? The two of you
can't do it.

131
00:06:59,067 --> 00:07:00,467
Who's going to pretend
to be the victim?

132
00:07:02,567 --> 00:07:03,167
Chief?

133
00:07:08,567 --> 00:07:09,800
Juliet,

134
00:07:09,933 --> 00:07:11,467
where are you going
to eat later?

135
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:13,100
Same place as before, why?

136
00:07:13,233 --> 00:07:15,733
Nothing, Juliet,
so we can avoid it.

137
00:07:15,900 --> 00:07:16,667
No!

138
00:07:16,800 --> 00:07:18,433
There's a lot of handsome guys
there!

139
00:07:18,567 --> 00:07:20,000
He's the one I want to avoid.

140
00:07:20,133 --> 00:07:20,767
Okay.

141
00:07:20,900 --> 00:07:22,100
Hey, it's the Village Chairman.

142
00:07:22,233 --> 00:07:24,433
Village Chairman,
what's the latest?

143
00:07:24,567 --> 00:07:26,267
What's the news about Kendra?
What happened?

144
00:07:26,400 --> 00:07:29,100
She has leptospirosis.

145
00:07:30,967 --> 00:07:32,200
Leptospirosis?

146
00:07:32,333 --> 00:07:34,633
Isn't that what you get
from the urine of rats?

147
00:07:34,767 --> 00:07:35,533
- Right.
- Yes.

148
00:07:35,667 --> 00:07:37,233
Or from floodwater.

149
00:07:37,367 --> 00:07:41,833
That's it. Kendra went into
the floodwaters.

150
00:07:41,967 --> 00:07:43,167
That's why.

151
00:07:43,300 --> 00:07:45,633
You two, I'll ask you to do
something.

152
00:07:45,767 --> 00:07:47,800
I get it, Village Chairman.

153
00:07:47,967 --> 00:07:51,333
We're going to conduct
an information drive

154
00:07:51,467 --> 00:07:52,900
here in the village.

155
00:07:53,033 --> 00:07:54,033
Perfect!

156
00:07:54,167 --> 00:07:57,000
And also to remind our village
members not to go

157
00:07:57,133 --> 00:08:00,200
into the floodwaters
if they have a wound.

158
00:08:00,333 --> 00:08:01,933
Or if it's unavoidable,

159
00:08:02,067 --> 00:08:05,167
you should always wear
protection like boots.

160
00:08:05,300 --> 00:08:06,033
Perfect!

161
00:08:06,167 --> 00:08:07,367
- Very good.
- Right?

162
00:08:07,500 --> 00:08:08,467
Is it good?

163
00:08:08,600 --> 00:08:09,733
- Yes.
- It's good.

164
00:08:09,867 --> 00:08:11,200
It's perfect.

165
00:08:12,833 --> 00:08:13,767
Told you so.

166
00:08:13,900 --> 00:08:15,667
What are you waiting for?

167
00:08:15,800 --> 00:08:17,633
Come on! Let's go!

168
00:08:17,767 --> 00:08:18,833
Let's go, girl.

169
00:08:24,333 --> 00:08:25,100
What, Enriquez?

170
00:08:25,233 --> 00:08:26,833
Are you sure
you'll be okay later?

171
00:08:28,567 --> 00:08:30,700
Yes, Sir. Why won't I be okay?

172
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:39,300
You and Lieutenant Samson
have a history, right?

173
00:08:43,533 --> 00:08:45,567
Noble is really a gossipmonger.

174
00:08:47,733 --> 00:08:49,267
I just mentioned to him

175
00:08:49,400 --> 00:08:52,967
that Lieutenant Samson and I
fought over a guy before.

176
00:08:53,100 --> 00:08:55,067
That was way back
at the academy.

177
00:08:55,233 --> 00:08:57,867
I didn't know
it had reached you, Sir.

178
00:08:59,100 --> 00:09:01,200
No, Noble didn't tell me
anything.

179
00:09:01,333 --> 00:09:05,033
All I know is that you're
batchmates at the academy.

180
00:09:05,167 --> 00:09:08,500
I noticed your body language
earlier.

181
00:09:08,633 --> 00:09:09,900
That's why I tested you.

182
00:09:11,133 --> 00:09:12,667
As for you,

183
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:14,100
you're so quick to get caught.

184
00:09:15,200 --> 00:09:17,400
I don't know about that girl.

185
00:09:17,533 --> 00:09:19,000
She doesn't know
how to move on.

186
00:09:20,733 --> 00:09:23,333
But are you sure you'll be okay
tonight?

187
00:09:23,467 --> 00:09:25,000
It's just the two of you
at the bar.

188
00:09:26,233 --> 00:09:27,400
Of course, Sir.

189
00:09:27,567 --> 00:09:31,800
We're not friends,
but she's a smart cop.

190
00:09:31,933 --> 00:09:35,300
Besides, Doctor Cecilia's
results on Amo

191
00:09:35,433 --> 00:09:36,367
haven't come out yet.

192
00:09:37,400 --> 00:09:40,267
This is good, so I can do
new things as well.

193
00:09:41,833 --> 00:09:44,667
If you're uncomfortable
with her,

194
00:09:44,800 --> 00:09:45,567
just let me know.

195
00:09:47,200 --> 00:09:49,133
So, I'll pick you up later?

196
00:09:49,267 --> 00:09:50,567
No need, Sir.

197
00:09:50,700 --> 00:09:51,900
I can manage.

198
00:09:52,933 --> 00:09:54,567
Just remember what Chief
ordered.

199
00:09:54,700 --> 00:09:56,300
Wear something suitable
for a night out in the bar.

200
00:09:56,433 --> 00:09:58,667
Don't wear cargo pants.

201
00:09:58,800 --> 00:10:00,067
Yes, Sir.

202
00:10:00,200 --> 00:10:02,000
I know. I can manage.

203
00:10:02,167 --> 00:10:02,933
I'll leave it up to you, okay?

204
00:10:03,067 --> 00:10:03,800
Yes, Sir.

205
00:10:03,933 --> 00:10:04,767
I'll see you there.

206
00:10:04,900 --> 00:10:05,567
Okay.

207
00:10:07,433 --> 00:10:09,567
Oh my, what should I wear?

208
00:10:14,433 --> 00:10:15,700
Where are they?

209
00:10:15,833 --> 00:10:16,933
What time is it?

210
00:10:19,733 --> 00:10:20,667
There's Conde.

211
00:10:22,467 --> 00:10:23,400
Where's Enriquez?

212
00:10:25,133 --> 00:10:26,100
We didn't go together.

213
00:10:26,233 --> 00:10:27,633
She said she'd go straight here,

214
00:10:27,767 --> 00:10:29,967
but she might be having second
thoughts.

215
00:10:30,100 --> 00:10:31,200
Because she doesn't have
anything to wear.

216
00:10:31,333 --> 00:10:32,933
She only has pants
in her wardrobe.

217
00:10:39,500 --> 00:10:40,467
Lieutenant Conde.

218
00:10:50,867 --> 00:10:51,533
Enriquez...

219
00:10:53,267 --> 00:10:54,367
you look sexy.

220
00:10:55,467 --> 00:10:57,467
Sir, not too much, Sir.

221
00:10:57,600 --> 00:11:01,033
When this case is over,
maybe we can have a date?

222
00:11:08,133 --> 00:11:09,233
Enriquez, you're late.

223
00:11:10,833 --> 00:11:13,267
Please, can we get serious here?

224
00:11:13,400 --> 00:11:15,267
Two women are missing.

225
00:11:15,400 --> 00:11:17,733
If we don't catch
the criminals tonight,

226
00:11:17,867 --> 00:11:19,200
their numbers will increase
even more.

227
00:11:20,233 --> 00:11:21,100
Sorry, partner.

228
00:11:22,700 --> 00:11:23,733
What, Enriquez?

229
00:11:23,867 --> 00:11:25,300
Are you ready?

230
00:11:25,567 --> 00:11:26,667
Ready, Sir.

231
00:11:26,967 --> 00:11:28,533
Then let's go?

232
00:11:28,667 --> 00:11:30,333
Bobby and I will go in.

233
00:11:30,467 --> 00:11:32,933
Wait for our call if we need
to be rescued.

234
00:11:33,067 --> 00:11:34,967
Okay, we'll just stay in the car
for now.

235
00:11:37,433 --> 00:11:38,333
Okay, Sir.

236
00:12:02,367 --> 00:12:03,133
Hi, Ma'am.

237
00:12:03,267 --> 00:12:04,467
Do you have a table number
already?

238
00:12:05,900 --> 00:12:07,867
Ma'am, I'm just asking if you
have a table number, Ma'am.

239
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:09,167
Bobby.

240
00:12:09,300 --> 00:12:10,767
Mister, sorry.

241
00:12:10,900 --> 00:12:12,700
I'll take care of you.
I'm sorry again.

242
00:12:12,833 --> 00:12:14,100
I'm sorry, Ma'am.

243
00:12:15,967 --> 00:12:16,933
Sorry, Mister.

244
00:12:19,967 --> 00:12:21,200
Bobby, what's with you?

245
00:12:21,333 --> 00:12:22,867
Can you do it?

246
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:25,033
We're just starting,
and you're already exposing us.

247
00:12:25,167 --> 00:12:26,533
Sorry, Ma'am.
I'm not used to this.

248
00:12:26,667 --> 00:12:27,767
Not used to where?

249
00:12:27,900 --> 00:12:29,600
Being touched by a man?

250
00:12:29,733 --> 00:12:30,800
Wait.

251
00:12:30,933 --> 00:12:33,867
Have you ever experienced going
to a place like this?

252
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:35,900
Yes, I'm used to this...

253
00:12:36,033 --> 00:12:38,933
Things like this, party, party.

254
00:12:40,400 --> 00:12:42,533
Bobby, stop. What are you doing?

255
00:12:42,667 --> 00:12:44,733
I doubt that you're telling
the truth.

256
00:12:44,867 --> 00:12:46,100
Sorry.

257
00:12:46,233 --> 00:12:46,867
Okay.

258
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:50,767
Criminals target those
who are alone.

259
00:12:50,900 --> 00:12:52,967
So we need to separate.

260
00:12:54,100 --> 00:12:54,667
Yes, Ma'am.

261
00:12:54,800 --> 00:12:55,600
But, Bobby...

262
00:12:55,733 --> 00:12:56,867
I'm telling you...

263
00:12:57,000 --> 00:12:59,967
if our mission gets compromised
because of you...

264
00:13:01,100 --> 00:13:03,367
I'll make sure
you get suspended.

265
00:13:20,633 --> 00:13:22,133
Okay, Auntie, you can pass
through.

266
00:13:24,100 --> 00:13:24,867
Auntie?

267
00:13:25,900 --> 00:13:26,667
Look at you,
you're wearing shades,

268
00:13:26,800 --> 00:13:27,933
even though it's dark here.

269
00:13:32,033 --> 00:13:33,000
How dare he call me "auntie?"

270
00:13:34,200 --> 00:13:35,933
I'm so pretty tonight.

271
00:13:36,067 --> 00:13:37,400
I've got makeup on.

272
00:13:37,533 --> 00:13:38,667
Excuse me, Ma'am.

273
00:13:40,300 --> 00:13:41,100
Thank you.

274
00:13:55,700 --> 00:13:57,267
I guess that's what
we're waiting for.

275
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:01,300
How can you say it's them?

276
00:14:01,433 --> 00:14:02,267
There, look.

277
00:14:03,500 --> 00:14:05,200
There were only three of them,
but they're using a van.

278
00:14:08,600 --> 00:14:10,167
They didn't turn off the engine.

279
00:14:11,333 --> 00:14:12,733
They must be waiting
for someone.

280
00:14:15,100 --> 00:14:16,733
You're good, Conde.

281
00:14:16,867 --> 00:14:18,033
It seems like it's them.

282
00:14:20,933 --> 00:14:22,200
Enriquez,

283
00:14:22,333 --> 00:14:23,167
Samson.

284
00:14:24,867 --> 00:14:26,600
Stay alert.

285
00:14:26,733 --> 00:14:28,567
Possible targets are coming up.

286
00:14:55,433 --> 00:14:56,033
Hi, Miss.

287
00:14:57,467 --> 00:14:58,467
Hi.

288
00:14:58,600 --> 00:14:59,700
Are you alone?

289
00:14:59,833 --> 00:15:01,600
Yes, I'm alone.

290
00:15:05,133 --> 00:15:06,567
Hi, Miss.

291
00:15:06,700 --> 00:15:07,800
Are you alone?

292
00:15:12,133 --> 00:15:13,633
Mister,

293
00:15:13,767 --> 00:15:15,600
do you see anyone with me?

294
00:15:16,933 --> 00:15:20,633
Oh my, Mister, I'm scared.

295
00:15:22,267 --> 00:15:23,967
Just kidding, Mister.

296
00:15:25,733 --> 00:15:26,500
I'm George.

297
00:15:26,633 --> 00:15:27,467
I'm Jen.

298
00:15:28,500 --> 00:15:29,800
My name is Bojart.

299
00:15:29,933 --> 00:15:30,967
Bojart...

300
00:15:32,967 --> 00:15:34,300
I'm...

301
00:15:34,433 --> 00:15:35,200
I'm...

302
00:15:36,600 --> 00:15:37,300
Kat.

303
00:15:37,433 --> 00:15:38,033
I'm Kat.

304
00:15:38,167 --> 00:15:39,133
Hi.

305
00:15:47,733 --> 00:15:49,433
It's been a while now
since the two went up,

306
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:51,933
but they still haven't
updated us.

307
00:15:52,067 --> 00:15:53,433
The two of them are just working
their way.

308
00:15:54,600 --> 00:15:55,933
Conde,

309
00:15:56,067 --> 00:15:57,100
trust the process.

310
00:15:59,433 --> 00:16:02,500
Enriquez, Samson,
what's the status there?

311
00:16:07,533 --> 00:16:08,700
Enriquez,

312
00:16:09,133 --> 00:16:10,367
what's the status there?

313
00:16:11,567 --> 00:16:12,967
<i> It's noisy here.</i>

314
00:16:13,100 --> 00:16:14,000
Actually.

315
00:16:14,133 --> 00:16:15,600
Do you want to go somewhere?

316
00:16:15,733 --> 00:16:16,600
Sure.

317
00:16:16,733 --> 00:16:17,867
It's noisy here, right?

318
00:16:19,433 --> 00:16:19,933
Yes.

319
00:16:20,067 --> 00:16:21,667
Yeah, it's pretty loud.

320
00:16:23,433 --> 00:16:29,133
Maybe you want to go somewhere
else so we can talk?

321
00:16:32,867 --> 00:16:34,333
Okay, okay, yeah.

322
00:16:34,467 --> 00:16:34,933
Is it okay?

323
00:16:35,067 --> 00:16:35,833
Yeah.

324
00:16:35,967 --> 00:16:37,100
Let's go.

325
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:41,933
Okay, let's go.

326
00:16:42,100 --> 00:16:42,833
After you.

327
00:16:42,967 --> 00:16:43,933
Okay.

328
00:16:48,767 --> 00:16:50,400
The elevator seems to be taking
so long.

329
00:16:50,533 --> 00:16:52,233
Do you want to take the stairs?

330
00:16:52,367 --> 00:16:54,500
Exciting. Let's go.

331
00:16:55,967 --> 00:16:57,100
Let's follow them.

332
00:16:57,233 --> 00:16:57,833
Them?

333
00:16:57,967 --> 00:16:58,433
Yeah.

334
00:17:01,233 --> 00:17:02,333
I heard from a source

335
00:17:02,467 --> 00:17:04,767
that Station 12 is having
a sting operation right now.

336
00:17:04,900 --> 00:17:07,433
Who are the people involved,
and where are they?

337
00:17:09,200 --> 00:17:10,067
Who's your source?

338
00:17:11,133 --> 00:17:13,367
A good reporter will not reveal
her sources.

339
00:17:14,500 --> 00:17:18,900
And a good reporter will not
jeopardize a police operation

340
00:17:19,033 --> 00:17:20,867
just to get a scoop.

341
00:17:21,000 --> 00:17:23,100
Once the operation is over,

342
00:17:23,233 --> 00:17:26,933
you can talk to my officer
as much as you can.

343
00:17:27,067 --> 00:17:30,633
But it should be after
the operation.

344
00:17:30,767 --> 00:17:33,333
- Chief? Chief, where is Tonyo?
- We need to talk to Tonyo.

345
00:17:33,467 --> 00:17:34,967
Tonyo is not here. Why?

346
00:17:35,100 --> 00:17:36,500
Sir, we need your help, Sir.

347
00:17:36,633 --> 00:17:37,400
- Why?
- Sir...

348
00:17:37,533 --> 00:17:38,800
that bridge in San Delfin
collapsed!

349
00:17:38,933 --> 00:17:39,933
Boss, it must have collapsed

350
00:17:40,067 --> 00:17:40,833
because of the heavy rains
for the past few days.

351
00:17:40,967 --> 00:17:42,933
We need your help.
An e-bike fell.

352
00:17:43,067 --> 00:17:44,400
- We can't get it.
- Leave those e-bikes alone.

353
00:17:44,533 --> 00:17:46,133
They don't follow
the traffic rules.

354
00:17:46,267 --> 00:17:49,800
Torres, we shouldn't choose
who to help.

355
00:17:50,200 --> 00:17:51,300
Just kidding, Sir.

356
00:17:52,167 --> 00:17:54,200
That's not a good joke.

357
00:17:54,333 --> 00:17:55,067
Sorry, Sir.

358
00:17:56,100 --> 00:17:57,467
Torres, De Jesus,

359
00:17:57,600 --> 00:18:01,400
go with them and coordinate
with the fire department

360
00:18:01,533 --> 00:18:02,867
and the municipality.

361
00:18:03,000 --> 00:18:03,833
Sir, yes, Sir!

362
00:18:04,867 --> 00:18:07,367
And you, Mira, you might want
to go too.

363
00:18:07,500 --> 00:18:10,633
This is the news that needs
to reach our fellow countrymen

364
00:18:10,767 --> 00:18:12,200
so they can be more careful.

365
00:18:12,333 --> 00:18:13,167
Okay, Sir.

366
00:18:13,300 --> 00:18:14,267
Yes, Sir.

367
00:18:14,400 --> 00:18:15,067
Okay.

368
00:18:20,800 --> 00:18:22,167
Are they okay there?

369
00:18:23,933 --> 00:18:26,667
What you should ask is
whether the suspects are okay.

370
00:18:26,800 --> 00:18:28,967
I'm sure Samson
will beat them up.

371
00:18:30,367 --> 00:18:31,767
Well, you have a point,

372
00:18:31,900 --> 00:18:34,033
Enriquez won't let them off
the hook.

373
00:18:49,200 --> 00:18:50,633
What's with you?

374
00:18:50,767 --> 00:18:53,267
Ouch! I can't wait any longer.

375
00:18:53,400 --> 00:18:54,400
Hey!

376
00:19:15,933 --> 00:19:17,267
Charlie, are you okay?

377
00:19:17,400 --> 00:19:19,033
I'm okay. Ask him.

378
00:19:20,633 --> 00:19:22,333
Conde, can I ask something?

379
00:19:23,700 --> 00:19:24,200
What?

380
00:19:25,267 --> 00:19:28,167
Are you and Sergeant Enriquez
dating?

381
00:19:31,067 --> 00:19:31,867
No, no.

382
00:19:33,133 --> 00:19:35,000
We just work together.

383
00:19:35,133 --> 00:19:36,500
Why did you ask?

384
00:19:38,400 --> 00:19:41,367
So if I ever I court her,

385
00:19:41,500 --> 00:19:44,100
at least I know I won't be
stepping on someone.

386
00:19:48,767 --> 00:19:51,533
So you were serious when you
asked her out earlier.

387
00:19:53,200 --> 00:19:56,000
I thought you and Lieutenant
Samson were together.

388
00:19:56,133 --> 00:19:56,867
Us?

389
00:19:57,000 --> 00:19:57,567
Yes.

390
00:19:57,700 --> 00:19:59,133
- No!
- No?

391
00:19:59,267 --> 00:20:00,300
I'm scared of her.

392
00:20:01,333 --> 00:20:02,433
And she has a boyfriend.

393
00:20:02,600 --> 00:20:04,333
We just don't know
who it is at the station.

394
00:20:09,567 --> 00:20:11,300
Enriquez...

395
00:20:11,433 --> 00:20:15,767
she's single, so if you want
to court her, it's up to you.

396
00:20:16,833 --> 00:20:17,933
But just a warning.

397
00:20:19,033 --> 00:20:20,633
She's a bit of a mean person.

398
00:20:21,733 --> 00:20:23,267
That's what I like,

399
00:20:23,400 --> 00:20:24,667
a challenge.

400
00:20:28,567 --> 00:20:29,533
What happened here?

401
00:20:29,667 --> 00:20:30,933
Bro, wake up!

402
00:20:31,067 --> 00:20:31,500
Bro?

403
00:21:14,033 --> 00:21:15,533
You thought I was going
to do that, didn't you?

404
00:21:18,900 --> 00:21:20,333
Charlie!

405
00:21:20,700 --> 00:21:21,500
Get down!

406
00:21:26,400 --> 00:21:27,600
Why did you throw my clutch bag?

407
00:21:27,733 --> 00:21:28,700
That's so expensive!

408
00:21:36,533 --> 00:21:37,300
Sorry.

409
00:21:37,433 --> 00:21:39,200
I didn't know.

410
00:21:39,333 --> 00:21:40,567
I thought it was fake.

411
00:21:40,700 --> 00:21:42,233
Do you think I'll buy something
that's fake?

412
00:21:42,400 --> 00:21:43,967
What if I hit you?

413
00:21:46,333 --> 00:21:47,933
Wait, where are our backups?

414
00:21:48,067 --> 00:21:48,933
I don't know.

415
00:21:49,067 --> 00:21:50,333
I've been contacting them
for a while now.

416
00:21:50,467 --> 00:21:52,433
Come on. Come on, let's go.

417
00:21:52,567 --> 00:21:54,600
Okay, wait.
Let me just get my bag.

418
00:21:54,733 --> 00:21:55,967
Hey, that's expensive too.

419
00:21:56,100 --> 00:21:56,867
P400.

420
00:21:57,000 --> 00:22:00,233
P400, expensive?
You're so cheap.

421
00:22:07,267 --> 00:22:08,633
Where are they?

422
00:22:08,767 --> 00:22:09,400
Right?

423
00:22:09,533 --> 00:22:10,900
They're gone. Let's go, quickly.

424
00:22:25,333 --> 00:22:26,733
Perfect timing.

425
00:22:28,667 --> 00:22:30,133
Where are the suspects?

426
00:22:30,267 --> 00:22:31,167
It's over, Sir.

427
00:22:33,933 --> 00:22:34,933
What do you mean that it's over?

428
00:22:39,733 --> 00:22:40,533
It's done.

429
00:22:41,567 --> 00:22:42,567
The five suspects are down.

430
00:22:44,133 --> 00:22:45,300
I'm sorry,

431
00:22:45,433 --> 00:22:46,533
Paloma's so talkative.

432
00:22:46,667 --> 00:22:48,633
He's asking a lot of questions
about Enriquez.

433
00:22:49,900 --> 00:22:50,733
Why, Sir?

434
00:22:50,867 --> 00:22:52,800
What are you asking about me?

435
00:22:52,933 --> 00:22:54,033
Me?

436
00:22:54,167 --> 00:22:55,200
Nothing.

437
00:22:55,333 --> 00:22:59,000
No, I told Conde not to worry
about the two of you

438
00:22:59,133 --> 00:23:02,867
because we're sure that you both
can handle it, right?

439
00:23:03,000 --> 00:23:05,133
All right, please report this
to the Chief.

440
00:23:05,267 --> 00:23:06,967
Hurry up!

441
00:23:07,100 --> 00:23:10,133
I still feel like fighting.
You two might get hit.

442
00:23:10,433 --> 00:23:11,500
Backup, huh?

443
00:23:14,467 --> 00:23:17,733
Me too, Sir, it feels like
the fighting wasn't enough.

444
00:23:24,500 --> 00:23:25,767
Good job, everyone!

445
00:23:27,567 --> 00:23:30,200
Thank you, Sir,
but Sergeant Enriquez

446
00:23:30,333 --> 00:23:32,100
and Lieutenant Samson were
the ones who actually caught

447
00:23:32,233 --> 00:23:33,167
the suspects.

448
00:23:33,300 --> 00:23:34,267
Yes, Sir.

449
00:23:34,400 --> 00:23:36,767
They literally don't need
our help anymore.

450
00:23:38,900 --> 00:23:39,867
With this arrest,

451
00:23:40,000 --> 00:23:42,400
we hope to identify the leader
of the syndicates

452
00:23:42,533 --> 00:23:45,233
and find the missing victims.

453
00:23:45,367 --> 00:23:47,333
Thank you very much, Chief,
for your help.

454
00:23:47,467 --> 00:23:49,100
Don't mention it, Lieutenant.

455
00:23:49,233 --> 00:23:52,367
As long as you need our help,
just say so.

456
00:23:53,767 --> 00:23:55,533
- Congratulations.
- Thank you, Sir.

457
00:23:55,700 --> 00:23:56,467
Congratulations.

458
00:23:57,667 --> 00:23:59,167
- Conde, congratulations.
- Thank you, Sir.

459
00:23:59,300 --> 00:24:00,800
Enriquez, congratulations.

460
00:24:00,933 --> 00:24:01,833
Thank you, Sir.

461
00:24:01,967 --> 00:24:04,100
- Lieutenant Conde.
- Thank you.

462
00:24:04,233 --> 00:24:05,200
Sergeant Enriquez.

463
00:24:07,133 --> 00:24:09,300
I know you defended me earlier,

464
00:24:09,433 --> 00:24:12,333
but that doesn't mean
we're quits already.

465
00:24:13,700 --> 00:24:14,500
I know.

466
00:24:21,333 --> 00:24:23,767
Sir, it's Doc Cecilia.

467
00:24:23,900 --> 00:24:25,933
The fingerprint analysis
on the gun

468
00:24:26,067 --> 00:24:28,767
used to kill Vice Mayor
Del Mundo is ready.

469
00:24:51,133 --> 00:24:53,000
What are you saying
about Reign being missing?

470
00:24:53,133 --> 00:24:54,500
Didn't you see her with her
luggage earlier?

471
00:24:54,633 --> 00:24:56,400
Her flight to Hong Kong
is today.

472
00:24:56,533 --> 00:24:57,700
I can't contact Reign.

473
00:24:57,833 --> 00:24:59,500
I'll look for her myself,
Godfather.

474
00:24:59,633 --> 00:25:00,967
I put a tracker on someone
earlier.

475
00:25:01,100 --> 00:25:03,533
Attorney, I'm sorry.
I didn't see you.

476
00:25:03,700 --> 00:25:04,233
Who?

477
00:25:04,367 --> 00:25:05,700
The prosecution lawyer.

478
00:25:05,833 --> 00:25:08,267
They're on their way to the
safehouse to talk to Selena.

479
00:25:08,400 --> 00:25:10,067
Hello, Selena.

480
00:25:10,200 --> 00:25:13,067
This is a copy of the CCTV
footage from 5 hours ago.

481
00:25:13,200 --> 00:25:14,800
I'd like you to trace a vehicle.

482
00:25:14,933 --> 00:25:15,833
A black van.

483
00:25:15,967 --> 00:25:18,733
Delta, alpha, x-ray, 3-6-4-9.

484
00:25:18,867 --> 00:25:20,300
Get back to me right away, okay?

485
00:25:23,867 --> 00:25:24,900
Do you want to go with him?

486
00:25:25,033 --> 00:25:26,200
No, please.

487
00:25:26,333 --> 00:25:27,233
- Help!
- Let's go.

488
00:25:27,367 --> 00:25:28,867
- Selena!
- Come in!

489
00:25:30,567 --> 00:25:31,400
Get down!

490
00:25:31,533 --> 00:25:32,033
Get down!

491
00:25:32,167 --> 00:25:33,400
Okay, get her in, quick!

492
00:25:33,533 --> 00:25:34,433
Let me go.

493
00:25:34,567 --> 00:25:37,033
I promise I won't say anything
against Amo.

494
00:25:37,200 --> 00:25:39,333
You can't get away,
do you understand?

495
00:25:39,467 --> 00:25:40,467
Get those ready.

496
00:25:40,600 --> 00:25:42,367
Later, we'll bring them
somewhere.

497
00:25:42,500 --> 00:25:43,200
What are you doing here?

498
00:25:43,333 --> 00:25:45,000
Sir, my godsister was kidnapped.

499
00:25:45,133 --> 00:25:47,400
I had Noble trace the van.
He said she was brought here.

500
00:25:47,533 --> 00:25:49,200
How about you, Sir?
What are you doing here?

501
00:25:49,333 --> 00:25:51,333
Selena was kidnapped
from the safehouse.

502
00:25:51,467 --> 00:25:52,900
She was also taken here.
